&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Would Get To Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account Director plays a key role in managing client relationships and supporting the strategic development of assigned account(s). This role is responsible for ensuring the successful delivery of programs, driving client satisfaction, and contributing to revenue growth opportunities.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Acting as a trusted partner to clients and an internal leader, the Account Director oversees account performance, supports financial management, and contributes to long-term account planning. The Account Director demonstrates strong client management experience, commercial acumen, and the ability to guide teams toward consistent, high-quality service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Contributions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Account Leadership &amp;amp; Client Growth&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact and strategic advisor for assigned clients&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong client relationships, ensuring long-term partnerships and continued growth opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain account plans and&amp;nbsp; develop a pipeline of growth opportunities across the client’s business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct monthly updates&amp;nbsp; and lead&amp;nbsp; quarterly account reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor monthly performance against annual targets, proactively identifying gaps and implementing actions to close them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor client satisfaction trends and proactively address issues, risks, and opportunities for improvement and growth&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
